    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nWe'd like to export a PDF version of the user manual (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39950), but `gen_help_html.lua` assumes an HTML output in several places.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nMake gen() take an output param\r\nRename gen_one() -> gen_one_html()\r\nRename visit_node() -> ts_node_to_html()\r\nAdd a mapping to gen() that calls the correct gen_one*() function.\r\n\r\nThis prepares the addition of new methods for Typst output.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Same idea as #37742 but this time with an incremental plan described at https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39950#issuecomment-4514025663.\r\n\r\nThere is a rough version of `node_to_typ()` at https://github.com/SqAtx/neovim/blob/gen_help_typ/src/gen/gen_help_html.lua, that can generate a passable `usr_01.typ`.\r\n\r\nI have not yet tested end-to-end with Hugo. The HTML files get generated without errors, at least.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/pull/479 will need to be merged immediately after this.\r\n\r\nOne thing I wanted to do but didn't is rename the file to `export_help_docs.lua` and generally gen* to export* (the script doesn't generate the help - it converts its format). Let me know if anyone has strong opinions about that - it can be done in the next commit.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-22T01:39:56Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39946#issuecomment-4514207985",
            "id": 4514207985,
